reviews.review:
There is such a thing as too much(!) fan service!
The worst star wars movie since 1999 or 1983 - I am still undecided!

142 minutes of fan service. Pacing was horrible - everything felt rushed and there was no room to breathe. Story lines were a mess and seemingly did not even connect to the previous two movies, or the rest of the saga for that matter.

Don‚Äôt believe the critic. Listen the fans that I have been since day one of the Saga. I happy/sad tears I the last half of the movie. It add so much more to the myth of the force. Thank you Jj. You saved Xmas.
I enjoyed the movie. the ending was very satisfying.

This was just a bunch of boring, meaningless one-liners and predictable fetch quests lead by bland characters that failed to develop unique personalities over the course of 3 movies. I never felt less attached to the characters of a Star Wars movie. Though it was not quite as offensively bad as The Last Jedi, it was pretty darn close. What a terrible disappointment...
I liked it and thought it was a well-done conclusion to the Skywalker Saga.

Each film since Empire has needed to reveal new aspects of the force in order to keep that mysterious part of the fantasy interesting, but with this installment we've finally reached the critical mass past which plot may not travel. A genuine story is no longer possible in a Star Wars Universe. I don't think anyone has ever understood what made the original work, including Lucas. Everyone should see this movie, because it's part of the whole mess, but also, it barely qualifies as a movie. When critics say "it's mostly exposition," here's a example of what they mean: this movie establishes stakes almost exclusively by having characters constantly point out that the next bit of incomprehensible plot must happen or everything will have been for nothing.

Edited my original review from 3 stars to 2 stars. After spending time thinking about the movie, there is just too many plot holes and stupid things that happen. I reaped hated The Last Jedi, but now I'm starting to think TLJ was the better made movie between these two. 

Original Review:
Hardly a satisfying conclusion of the Skywalker/Star Wars Saga, but it is a conclusion..... 

Actually is was very surprising how much was concluded in this movie.  There is actually nowhere to go from this point forward. It seems if Disney is going to make more Star Wars movies, it will have to be like Rogue One or The Mandalorian. Just filling in time gaps between the 9 episodes. 

The pacing of this movie is very fast and plot development is very convenient. All the characters have deep connections with each other, all which apparently have developed off screen.

Better than the Last Jedi, but not by much.
Good ending to a great saga!
